  "body": "[comment]: # (Please replace ... with your information. Remove < and >)\r\n\r\n### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user, I want to control over how mail servers are chosen.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nBy default Status will auto-select a mail server. It status encounters problems it will switch servers. \r\n \r\nStatus will \"pin\" a mail server if a user selects a mail server, but there is no way to unpin it. Also, there is no UI indication if a mail server selection is set to auto or pinned.\r\n\r\nThis is quite confusing!\r\n\r\nTo help bring clarity we can introduce a explicit \"select mail servers automatically\" toggle. If this is on then Status will try to slect the best mail server. The mail servers are greyed out to indicate they cannot be chosen.\r\n\r\nIf \"auto\" is turned off then the mail servers switch back to regular colours and the selection is sticky.\r\n\r\nHere is a quick mockup\r\n\r\n<img width=\"706\" alt=\"screen shot 2018-10-18 at 5 50 39 pm\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/116099/47167522-04927280-d2ff-11e8-8185-d91f4544ae99.png\">\r\n\r\nTHIS IS NOT A DESIGN, but rather a concept sketch. Would love to see @errorists @denis-sharypin take a crack at it.\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nAn auto option that will select mail servers automatically.\r\nWhen turned off the mail servers can be chosen by the user.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nConfusing auto/pin behaviour merged.\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n* Operating System: All\r\n",
